caption: I’m a DoorDasher and Dumpling Darling is consistently backed up and understaffed. Every order I have ever gotten from here takes at LEAST 30 minutes after I’ve already arrived. Extremely frustrating. Don’t order delivery from here unless you’ve got an hour to spare.

This has quickly become a new favorite takeout place of mine. I honestly crave the brussel sprouts multiple times a week. The maple is my favorite with the Korean BQ being a close second, occasionally the Korean BQ ones are a little too saucy. The Thai curry bao bun is my favorite, so soft and the filling is delightful. I wish it was included in the darling deal with the other bao buns. The fried Korean Chicken dumpling is delicious and is also sadly not on the darling deals list. One of my absolute favorite qualities of this restaurant is the packaging. They use eco-friendly, food-safe cardboard for delivery. I would happily order from them weekly, "plastic guilt" free.

I was really hoping this place would be good because dumplings are my favorite food. The menu sounded amazing, but the food itself was terrible. I had a combo with a green curry bun, vegetable tempura, japchae, and lamb dumplings. The curry bun was overpowering. The amounts of curry in there was nasty, and I love thai curry. The vegetable tempura was not tempura. It was sad pieces of cauliflower, dipped in a boatload of batter, and fried. The texture was super greasy and dense, while tempura should be delicate and crunchy. And it was raw in the middle as you can see in the photo. The japchae was so old. It had no veggies at all, and was giant dried out clumps of overcooked noodles. You can see how bad it was in the picture with the huge clump by my fork. The lamb dumplings were one of the weirdest flavors I've put in my mouth, and it was really off putting. My husbands had the fried rice, soup dumplings, and hoisin pork bun. The fried rice was old and dry. The soup dumplings weren't soup dumplings. They had no soup inside at all. We didn't even bother trying the pork bun. We went inside and asked for a refund for the first time in my life. Nothing was edible. The cashier was super nice about it though! I had high hopes for this place with the reviews but was very disappointed. I seriously suggest some quality control in the kitchen, as too much of the food was old.

To be straightforward: this food is not at all worth the listed price. The wife and I tried a couple types of dumplings, two different buns, fried rice, and japchae noodles. The dumplings were overcooked and fell apart as soon as they were picked up, and the fillings were either flavorless or too overwhelming. We split one bun open (green curry) and tried it at the same time. Both of us nearly spat it out. The only thing we could taste was the curry, and there was so much it burned our throats from the one bite.  I'll save going on about this so I don't sound like a brat, but it was bad. I only give this place a 2 star review because the lady working the counter was understanding and gave us a refund after the few bites we tried. Either we had a bad experience, or the 5 star reviewers haven't had good dumplings before.

Definetly a lot of flavor, which I was pleasantly surprised. It was definitely different from the typical cuisine you find in town so I had to check Dumpling Darling out!  There was a huge variety of dumplings so I tried the sampler and although all very flavorful it wasn't what I imagined, there was definitely their own individual touch or flavor to each of them. For example the periogis had the traditional filling but with a potsticker type of wrapper still good but wasn't what I imagined. I didn't know if I like it or not but wanted to give it a fair assessment so went back again before I left town to try some more dishes.  This time I tried something different and got the buns, rice and noodles combo selection they had. The texture of the buns was perfect, honestly wasn't crazy about the filling. I would've went traditional or completely alternative and I think that's might be it. For example traditional periogis with traditional wrap OR try the buns with maine lobster filling. I am giving it a  4 star just due to personal preference, after my second try, I would prefer it more traditional or go wild. Just my own preference.  Also living in a bigger market now I really don't find the prices as high, I think they are priced appropriately. I come back to visit my alma mater quite often and always try some place new when I am in town. This was a nice find and I definetly recommend it.

Dumping Darling is one of my go-to’s for Iowa City takeout. I had never had japchae before trying Dumpling Darling and it’s quickly become one of my favorite meals. The staff is super nice and I’ve always had great experiences with the restaurant. Definitely check it out when you’re in Iowa city!

I thought that was great business and just kind in general. The second time I went, my order was correct and hot and delicious! All of the dumplings we tried were fabulous and the Brussels sprouts were so good! We'll definitely order from there again when we return to Iowa City.

First of all, there are no photos, as it is not fair to this Dumpling Darling to show an empty establishment by no fault of their own.  That being said, I would wholeheartedly recommend Dumpling Darling for their wide selection of exotic foods.  Located in downtown Iowa City, this cozy establishment has a varied and interesting menu.  We selected an order of the Pork and Cabbage Dumplings, the Potato Pierogies, and the Darling Deal #1 (2 kids of dumpling with 2 sides).  For the Darling Deal #1 I selected the Pork and Cabbage Dumplings, the Korean Chicken dumplings, with a side of vegan Kimchi and Korean BBQ Brussels Sprouts.  The Pork and Cabbage Dumpling are pan steamed, then fried in the same pan (it seemed--I did not observe the preparation).  VERY TASTY dumpling with a good ration of meat and veg, and seasoned well.  The wrapper for them is very thin, which allows more of the flavor of the filling to come through.  The Korean Chicken dumpling looked like it was quickly deep fried (again, I didn't see them getting prepared).  Needless to say, there were delicious.  The outside was thin and crispy, and the chicken inside was moist and flavorful.  And I don't know the sauce it was covered with, but it was amazing.  A perfect compliment to the dumplings.  The vegan kimchi was very good, but I would have liked a little more spice to it.  The Korean BBQ Brussels Sprouts are out of this world.  Dumpling Darling, if you can get my Brussels Sprouts Hating Wife to try two of your amazing side dish, you must know that you are doing something to perfection.  The Potato Pierogies were good, but to us, they were not pierogies.  We come from a town with a huge Polish population, and we've all grown up on our version of piergoies.  All in all, Dumpling Darling did not disappoint us one bit.  We loved the food, and the drinks were amazing as well.  Definitely will come back again.

Dumpling Darling actually does live up to the hype and it's 10 times better than the frozen stuff.  If you are a fan of dumplings in Iowa City, this is definitely the spot for you. Pro Tip Secret Menu - The Leo.  Last weekend I went into Dumpling Darling and had one of the best things that i’ve ever eaten.  Not - at - Dumpling Darling - at all.  I went in about 2 AM, and Chef Leo was there.  Dizzied by all the choices for the late night menu - I decided that I would pull a Netflix move and do something crazy.  I looked at the Chef and I told him,” I want you to make whatever you would want to eat.” He nodded in agreement, and thought for a moment.  I had to clarify, “I want you to make this with passion - I want you to be proud of what you put on that plate. I want you to make a meal that you will wake up tomorrow and you can say to your friends, ‘I made the BEST meal of my life last night’.”  His eyes wided a bit, and then a devilish grin appeared on his face, “Ok.” He said, with a nod.  As the woman working the cashier asked, “Will that be for here or to go?” I saw the wheels started turning in his head, as this Dumpling Darling turned into Chef’s Table. It was like watching a master at work.  “For here.” I said, as I got the attention of the Chef, “I’m going to sit right here, and i’m going to tell you, to your face, exactly what I think of what you make tonight.”  Well . . .  Remember that scene in Ratatouille, when the critic takes a bite of the food - well it was like that, if he was also in that fighting scene from Endgame.  That’s how much flavor this korean chicken wing had. There were levels. There were conversations with spices. There was heart. This was the Coach Carter of korean chicken wings.  But I said nothing.  See, I was sure that apart of this was a product of the hype. As the Chef looks on, I determine I need to eat another.  I could have sworn I had Hermionie’s time-turner … because by george of the jungle …. I was back at the start of this incredible epic of a korean chicken wing. In fact - It was even better the second time.  Out of this fever dream of flavors, I looked up and I nodded, “This is one of the best things that I have ever eaten...”  He gives a NBA finals championship mini celebration to himself - as I dive in for the other four wings of waverly place.  I’ve had food all over the world - and of the top favorites that I have range from, a crab cake from Aruba, a cowboy ribeye from California, Unagi from Sugarfish in NYC, an order of fish and chips from a corner pub in Edinburgh, Scotland, etc. - and now this order of Korean Chicken Wings from Dumpling Darling in Iowa City, IA, by Chef Leo.  He put himself on that plate (it was on one of those bowl boat things, but you get it). I have never been more inspired by food in my life, but it wasn’t about the food. It was about the precision, the passion, and the purpose of this guys life that he decided that - today, he had time. I don’t know if this is his full time job - but Leo is GOING places in his life.  As more people walked in, I kept telling them the story, and people were clamoring for him to make them one.  I get up to leave, and realize I never ask his name, “Leo”, he says.  I give him a point - youu know that point of someone who just did the dang thing, “I’m proud of you Leo.” He gives a nod - and the episode of Top Chef roles the credits.  At the time, I just said order ‘The Chef Special’ - but having a few days of distance, it’s called the Leo.  Whatever you do today, whatever you think you can’t do today - do yourself a favor, order this, so that you can be reminded there is a ‘Leo’ in all of us, just waiting to accept the challenge.  Thanks Leo - It won’t be a meal that I will ever forget.

Very good food and nice concept. Prices were reasonable. First of all, there are no Korean food restaurants in Des Moines which is sad. So having a restaurant the serves more Korean food on the menu was a plus for me.  My only suggestion is to make Korean foods without Americanising it. Sorry if I am traditional Korean foodie comsumer, but the Korean restaurants I patronize in MN didn't change the cuisine to fit the tastes of the public. You'll be surprised by people who will enjoy "authentic" foods.  Suggestion for the Kimchi fried rice - cut the Kimchi smaller and drain/wring out the juices before pan frying the rice. Add Kimchi juices as needed when cooking. Some Korean mother add in diced Spam into the fried rice. Many did this as Spam was introduced to Korean back during the Korean War. Stopped here for dinner while visiting the university. Was looking for something unique, something that was not pizza and burgers and was not disappointed. Ordered two "buns" and a flight of dumplings. It was enough to feed two people and the variety of flavors was awesome!  Very yummy.
Food is amazing, and service is very friendly! It's a must enjoy spot in Iowa City!
This place is the best! We drive an hour from grinnell just to eat here! The owners are so down to earth and they love what they do! Well worth giving it a try!!!!

I loved the Kimchi mandu...I really like it that they have so many vegetarian options, and the fusion that they've introduced into the flavours works really well with the dumpling concept. It can work as a quick snack, or a meal of you order enough.
We got banh mi with pulled pork. Really good! I also like that they're very eco-conscious. I'm looking forward to going again while we're here.

Amazing. I love this restaurant. Staff is always so friendly and amazing, and always willing to give recommendations and help out with the menu. Food is incredible as well! Lots of different choices and variety, and everything is so good! Probably my favourite restaurant in Iowa City, would highly recommend.
I think this the only place you can get pierogi in Iowa City, and their pierogi is delicious. I've also had their lamb dumplings and they were amazing.
Delicious food, loved the pork and cabbage dumplings, the Korean bbq plate and the japchae. Beware the red paste is very spicy!

I had the dumpling flight and cherry cream soda delivered via Chomped. Overall the dumplings were delicious, and the various containers were labeled with the correct pairing sauce. The only thing that detracted a star away from this was the fact that the soup dumplings had no actual soup in them! You could taste the pork and a hint of broth, but that delicious mouthful of soup you'd expect was nowhere to be found.
The dumplings were delicious. The buns we're fantastic. It was overall a great experience. The staff were extremely helpful and friendly.
Great food and friendly staff. It is a little small, so you cant take big groups. But food came out quick and was excellent

Great food
Yummy

Wow! I found this place by accident and I couldn't be happier! Cozy, friendly nook. Classic rock overhead. And the food is amazing. Pierogies to rival my grandma's. Korean chicken dumplings with a not-too-sweet sauce. The cheddar potato soup was delish and had a hearty mouth feel. Although pretty full, I'm glad that I tried the dessert: peanut butter marshmallow rice crispy dumplings. Laugh if you want to, but mmmm.  2 thumbs up.
Different and good! They have not only dumplings but tasty steamed buns too. They do a lot of fusion menu items as well. They have a soda machine that has unique flavors including cherry cream.
Flavors need more zip!  Or gochujang....
It was something different. Tried the fried dumpling flight. A few we really liked, a couple were not to our taste. Cool selection of organic soda. Good service.
great staff and welcoming atmosphere! good comfort food with unique flavors
Awesome food, wish I could get to downtown more.

Amazing! Simply amazing. We got a few different kinds of dumplings and a bao bun. Our favorites were the Korean Chicken fried dumpling and the Pork and Cabbage steamed dumpling. So delicious and flavorful. We will definitely return and tell all of our friends. If you live in the Iowa City area and haven’t been here you are missing out! I will say we didn’t eat in because I wasn’t feeling well so we went for the carry out option, but the inside looks very cute and clean. The staff members were so friendly and kind enough to take the time to write the food labels on all of the boxes for us. What impressed me most was the carry out packaging. We try and live a low-impact lifestyle and try to stay away from packaging that can’t be recycled or composted. Everything was in a brown paper bag in brown boxes! The only plastic was the sauce containers. So glad to have found a business that is taking the time to think about better packaging for the environment. Great job, Dumpling Darling. We will return soon!

When my whole family is happy eating somewhere I take it as a sign. I loved the noodles I ordered and the little tastes I had of the other dishes at our table. Friendly staff, well-designed but unpretentious decor. We'll be back.
Such a cute little place! I've only had the Potato Perogies and the Pork and Cabbage dumplings, but they were both very good!
Oh, hells yeah. The dining room is sort of small & it's a little steamy. We had some Chinese dumplings, some Russian mini pierogi things, & kimchi. Cheap, quick, amazing.

I ordered my food off Grubhub at 11:20 and got my food at 11:50 (it was still very warm). I got the Mac and Cheese and Kimchi dumplings (the small size has 5 dumplings each). The Mac and Cheese was good, but had a sweeter dough than I would have expected/liked for what I expected to be a more savory dumpling. The Kimchi was very good! Both sauces were also good. Great little place with awesome delicious food! I did not like that I had to kill 4 flies while eating inside the restaurant though. Please work on that. Would definitely like to see their extended menu at their branch at Newbo Cedar Rapids. I love Korean food!

Food is just decent, and servings are a bit expensive for the price. Coming from an Asian background the dumplings served here are not at all authentic, especially for the filling options they have for the dumplings. As for their Korean food you can find a better Korean place downtown.

Fantastic dumplings, brisket and menu overall. Friendly owners and staff. Creative and varied menu. Great location.

I've had these dumplings before they had their own shop, so i wanted to check out their own place. We went here for lunch, i got the kimchi mandu steamed dumplings, my friend got the perogis, and i got my boyfriend the avocado rangoons to bring him while he was working. OMG, everything was AWESOME. My friend and boyfriend wouldn't stop talking about them all day. The place is REALLY tiny, so seating is limited, i suggest getting food to-go, or just waiting around for a seat. It's a quick lunch so seats open up quickly but you have to be fast! I'm a vegetarian so i really appreciated all of their vegetarian friendly options!
Really enjoyed the green curry dumpling and rangoon. Tasty!

To be sincere, this is the worst Asian food I've ever eaten.  From the dumplings to the japchae, etc...it's an insult to korean/Chinese cuisine because it does not reflect what these food are supposed to reflect.  I usually do not give reviews but I had to because I was deceived by the 4.3 stars noted for this restaurant.  I had to apologize to my children who had to eat it because they are taught not to waste food. So for people who want authentic Asian dumplings etc, this is not the place.  For those who don't care...that's where the 4.3 stars are from.
This restaurant was sooo bad. The only reason I'm giving it one star is because of the drink. I know I will NEVER be returning.

Had a great experience at Dumpling Darling; the food, service, and atmosphere were all excellent. My wife and I were passing through Iowa City on a long drive and our stop there for lunch was a great decision. I can't remember all the food we had, but the Lesley's Lamb, Avocado Rangoon, and Bulgogi Beef bao buns were especially delicious. I've eaten countless orders of dumplings (mandu) in Korea, and Dumpling Darling's offerings are a delicious take on this Korean staple.
The food is so good and I love that they're open so late on the weekend! 🙌🏼

The food is always made to order fresh and  taste amazing.  They have a large  unique  variety of different things on the menu and daily specials. Also I love their fountain sodas are Ginger brew, Lemongrass, Cola, Cherry cream soda and Sweet Tea.
Clean, friendly, fast service and delicious food!
Great place if you like fried food, not so if you like dumplings.
Great fussion dumplings!  This place is the best!  The owner Leslie is awesome and a super nice lady!
It's so amazing! The Korean Chicken dumplings are like little packets of joy.

The food here sucks. I am a Nepali and we do eat momo (dumplings) a lot. We also make it ourselves. Even get the pack from Walmart which we only need to heat over steam. We ordered from here because we were drunk to drive and did not have the wraps to make it at home. So we got it delivered through orderup. I got the Lamb and the Bison(which is apparently supposed to be Nepali style), oh hell no. Its just dry meat with literally nothing in it. We make it with about 15 other ingredients plus the meat.

I wasn't sure how I'd feel when I went here, it was either going to be very good or very 'meh'. I am delighted to say this was a VERY good on many fronts! The cashier greeted us with a smile and was very friendly. She gave us a run down of our options because we really couldn't decide what we wanted and she was honest and didn't try to sell us on what we were eating. We ordered the lamb steamed dumpling, Korean Chicken dumpling, Perogies and dessert dumplings to get an even sample. The food came out amazingly fresh but much to my dismay very hot (I was hungry and am often impatient, needless to say i burnt my tongue... I deserved that :P ) All the dumplings had a wonderful fresh taste, good flavors and didn't feel too heavy. I don't do well with spicy so I was leery of the Korean Chicken but it had just the right heat that wasn't over powering. Our dessert (it rotates I'm told) was an ice cream filled mochi. It was divine. The prices are a bit high but you get a decent amount. I paid 14 total for two orders of dumplings and a soda. The soda is also incredibly amazing, zero corn syrup (I have a corn food allergy so it's a total win for me!) and they taste amazing. The environment is certainly a bit cramped for my tastes but it's cozy and you can always get your food to go or order frozen dumplings to make later which is awesome.  Food is a language and I have to say I love what they were saying. :)
Dumplings in Iowa!
I took my food to go.  I think it would have been better to eat it there.  Next time:).
